Last time #Bitcoin‚ÄØ‚ÄØ‚ÄØ was ~69K US Dollars, it was ~85K Canadian Dollars.

Bitcoin is ~69,700 USD today, but it's 95k CAD...

Bitcoin's price in CAD increased 12%, but it's only up 1% in USD.

This is a combination of:

1) The Canadian dollar being debased MUCH faster than the US Dollar (supply increasing)
2) Fewer people wanting to hold CAD over USD (demand decreasing)

The Canadian dollar is trending to 0 much faster than the US dollar in terms of Bitcoin.

cleaned_data.original_text:
A lot of people have tried to influence my decision making on #Bitcoin over the past few years. 

My friends told me I was stupid for buying at $69K. My family told me I was crazy for hodling at $15K. 

Financial advisors told me it was a ponzi and to run away. My girlfriend told me I was in a cult on the internet. 

My brother-in-law said it peaked and he sold. My cousin sold his to pay for a wedding. My dad sold his for real estate. My mom told me to sell at $45K.

The most incredible thing is no one ever told me that it is the best returning asset of the last 15 years. 

No one told me that the world is becoming digitized and finance is the next domino to fall. 

No one cared enough to understand inflation, monetary policy, characteristics of money or how all fiat currencies go to zero. 

No one wanted to put in the work besides me. 

Excuse me when I get emotional with people who know next to nothing about #Bitcoin. 

They didn‚Äôt do the fucking work. We did. 

I will not falter and no one will break my confidence. I will not stop accumulating the winner in this decades long play. 

I will burn bridges, run relationships into the ground and sacrifice everything for what I believe in. Nothing stops this train. 

I know what I own and where it is going. 

I made this post to blow off some steam. Tired of the constant doubt from everyone around me. This shit makes me want to go silent. 

A big fuck you to all the doubters who never took a minute to study what they own nothing of. 

Enjoy getting left behind for the next 2 years. It‚Äôs going to be bloody fucking great watching these bears get slaughtered on the way up. 

- Therapist

In its simplest form, trading is a pattern recognition game. 

3/3 times the market has been VERY clear that cycle tops come 12-18 months after the #Bitcoin halving. 

Stubborn mid-curvers will foolishly try to out smart the clear pattern in the chance they can "be proven right" and have that "told you so" moment. Unfortunately they can be very vocal and take there followers down with them. 

Crypto is still an INCREDIBLE asymmetric bet. My advice, don't overthink it.

Sit spot, get involved in a community, stick to a take profit strategy, and sit quietly in a room and watch the numbers go up without overclicking buttons.

cleaned_data.original_text:
All roads lead to Bitcoin. Few outside of bitcoin circles understand this. 

Here‚Äôs what I mean üëá

#BTC is selling off because Wall St and Main St both treat #Bitcoin as a ‚Äúrisk-on‚Äù asset.

If you‚Äôre none the wiser, this makes sense. Other risk assets, like tech stocks and small caps tend to sell off when interest rates are anticipated to be ‚Äúhigher for longer‚Äù because higher rates create tighter conditions for these companies to operate. Money is harder to come by (banks aren‚Äôt lending as often when rates are high), and earnings have to be discounted against a higher risk free rate. The more interest an investor can get by parking cash in a money market fund, the less appetite they have for risky assets. As investors take risk off the table, all volatile assets take a hit. 

But peel back the onion a few more layers and you‚Äôll see that these conditions (higher rates) set the table for an epic Bitcoin bull runüëá

All governments have a spending problem which has resulted in a gigantic pile of un-payable debt. In the US alone, some $7 trillion of debt must be refinanced at these higher rates this year. Higher rates make the debt tougher to service and it also leads to reduced economic activity and lower tax receipts (income) for the government. This widens the annual deficit because they never cut spending while their costs rise and their income falls. 

Since deficits are paid for with newly-issued debt, and newly issued debt is increasingly paid for with freshly printed fiat, then higher rates simply create the conditions for more money printing. Whenever new money is printed, some of it finds its way into Bitcoin. This is already playing out in the sense that Bitcoin has been on a tear since 2023 despite generational high interest rates. Hardly anyone thought that would happen. It happened because Bitcoin is actually the ultimate ‚Äúrisk-off‚Äù asset‚Äô

It‚Äôs checkmate for the Fed. No matter what they do, it‚Äôll be #Bitcoin for the win.

cleaned_data.original_text:
I am not here to trade Bitcoin or Bitcoin-related assets.

I am here to save in #Bitcoin.

What does that mean exactly?

It means that I am using Bitcoin as my unit of account.

Every month,

every USD that comes in is converted to BTC,

which,

over the years,

has substantially increased my purchasing power.

It will continue to increase because fiat is known as a debasing currency.

Every post, every essay, every image is a reflection of this thesis.

I am not here for short-term gains or short-term trades.

I am here to use the predictable monetary system until it achieves its goal, or until it becomes unpredictable.

If it becomes unpredictable, I will delve deeply into studying other assets that could be predictable.

For now,

no such assets exist.

Bitcoin is the most longitudinal, safe, decentralized asset/monetary system/property that is predictable to the unit.

-MDB

who cares?

cleaned_data.original_text:
#Bitcoin corrections can be worrisome especially when we've been spoiled by no 30% corrections the entire cycle.

But even with ETFs present, they must occur.

Price has yet to retest the 20-week EMA at now $55,600 which would provide stability for price going forward.

Data has reached overextended levels on many sources making this a much needed pullback.

As long as Bitcoin continues to retest this moving average, we can see a nice smooth curve like 2017 to the top.

Failing to retest begins a parabola, which typically end in 1 - 5 months.

Everything we're seeing is healthy for price action!
